Frank Ribery may have bounced back to existence. The old player who had recently left Bayern has a new club. Also, Lazio have presented their two latest signings: Andre Anderson and Manuel Lazzari. According to Calcio Mercato, Atletico Madrid are keen on the signing of Rodrigo de Paul from Valencia.


Vicent Kompany has lasted just four matches in charge as coach of Anderlecht, with the Belgian replaced by Simon Davies in the dugout. The former Manchester City player will continue as a player.


EL Golazo de Gol claim that Barcelona would stand a better chance of signing Neymar if they were to include Samuel Umtiti as part of the deal as Paris Saint-Germain are keen on the French defender.



			
